    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain your<strong> sweetcorn</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-spiced-pea-and-corn-fritters-with-fried-sesame-egg/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>ground cumin</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and<strong> ginger & garlic paste</strong> with your <strong>egg[s] </strong>(reserving 1 egg per person for later!) in a bowl</p><p>Add the <strong>drained sweetcorn</strong> and your <strong>blanched peas</strong> with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up until fully combined \u2013 this is your <strong>fritter mixture</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-spiced-pea-and-corn-fritters-with-fried-sesame-egg/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pan is hot, spoon the<strong> fritter mixture</strong> into the pan, roughly divided into 2 per person and cook for 4 min on one side, then 2 min on the other until golden and cooked through \u2013 these are your<strong> Indian-style pea & sweetcorn fritters</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-spiced-pea-and-corn-fritters-with-fried-sesame-egg/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half</strong> your <strong>black sesame seeds</strong>, then crack the reserved <strong>egg[s]</strong> into the pan and sprinkle the <strong>remaining black sesame seeds</strong> over the top with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame egg[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-spiced-pea-and-corn-fritters-with-fried-sesame-egg/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the egg[s] and fritters are cooking, bash your <strong>cucumber</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and chop it roughly</p><p>Tip: Bash the cucumber in its bag to avoid mess. By bruising the cucumber, the water is drawn out more easily!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-spiced-pea-and-corn-fritters-with-fried-sesame-egg/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Roll your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Loosen your<strong> red chilli relish </strong>with a squeeze of<strong> lemon juice -</strong> this is your <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-spiced-pea-and-corn-fritters-with-fried-sesame-egg/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>bashed cucumber</strong> to a medium bowl </p><p>Add a little of the <strong>sweet chilli sauce</strong>, a<strong> </strong>squeeze of <strong>lemon juice, </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong>, a small drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and toss together \u2013 this is your<strong> cucumber salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/indian-spiced-pea-and-corn-fritters-with-fried-sesame-egg/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Indian-style pea & sweetcorn fritters</strong>, stacked, with the <strong>cucumber salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Top the fritters with a <strong>sesame egg </strong>and drizzle the <strong>sweet</strong> <strong>chilli sauce</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
